     ,"DETECTOR":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4codes":[{"code":"BF3", "dict":"DETECTOR", "idict":22,"hlp":"Boron Trifluoride neutron detector"}
	    ,{"code":"HE3SP", "dict":"DETECTOR", "idict":22,"hlp":"Helium-3 spectrometer"}]
	,"x4freetext":[" The 3HeBF3 Giant Barrel (HeBGB) neutron"
		,"detector. While HeBGB provides nearly 4pi coverage,"
		,"having a nearly constant absolute efficiency of"
		,"0.075(12) for isotropic neutrons, MCNP6 simulation"
		,"results show a dependence of the efficiency on the"
		,"neutron angular distribution."]
	}
      ]
     ,"SAMPLE":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4code":{"Nucl":"6-C-13","ENR":0.99}
	,"x4freetext":[" The 13C target, produced by Arizona"
		,"Carbon Foil, Inc. via electron-beam evaporation of"
		,"carbon enriched to >99% 13C onto a copper substrate,"
		,"was determined to have a 13C thickness (areal density)"
		,"of nt = (1.12+-0.05)*10**18 atoms/cm2 via alpha-"
		,"elastic scattering, alpha energy-loss measurements, and"
		," a scan of the 1.053 MeV 13C(alpha,n) resonance."]
	}
      ]
     ,"METHOD":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4code":null
	,"x4freetext":["The beam passed through a 0.5-cm-diameter gold plated"
		,"collimator located approximately 48 cm upstream of"
		,"the target location and was impinged on a 13C target"
		,"located on a gold-plated ladder at the center of the"
		,"HeBGB moderator. The incident charge was measured by"
		,"summing the beam current of the electrically isolated"
		,"target ladder and target chamber within HeBGB. To"
		,"ensure the entirety of the beam was on target, at"
		,"each measurement energy the beam was first tuned"
		,"through an empty frame in the target ladder and the"
		,"integrated beam charge Qalpha was recorded using a"
		,"downstream Faraday cup. At periodic energy spacings,"
		,"measurements were performed on a copper substrate"
		,"identical to the backing used for the 13C targets in"
		,"order to as certain the neutron background. Neutrons"
		,"were detected using the 3He and BF3 neutron-sensitive"
		,"proportional counters. A pulser, adjusted to provide"
		,"a signal outside of the neutron spectrum, was used to"
		,"monitor the proportional counter deadtime and"
		,"therefore the live fraction flive of the data"
		,"acquisition."]
	}
      ]
     ,"ANALYSIS":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4code":null
	,"x4freetext":["In order to calculate the energy at the center of the"
		,"target, for which we report a cross section, stopping"
		,"power based on the world data and commonly used"
		,"theoretical stopping powers at these energies was"
		,"employed, adopting the difference between the largest"
		,"and smallest stopping powers for the stopping power"
		,"uncertainty and the median of these extremes as the"
		,"stopping power. The cross section at each energy is"
		,"calculated according to the thin-target approximation,"
		,"where the reported energy is the center-of-mass"
		,"energy at the center of the target."]
	}
      ]
